in 1916, William Boeing laid the foundation of
what would become the iconic name in aviation history, Boeing,
a engineering-first company which then soaring to an unimaginable levels in decades.

but it was in 1969, when Boeing release the Boeing 747,
which redefine air travel.
it hailed as the queen of the skies and plane that shrunk the world.
it revolutionized the way people moved across continents.

fast forward to 2024,
now this once mighty company is facing a turbulence of different kind.